nd discover the joy of science. It will empower you to think more objectively, see through the fog of your own preexisting beliefs, and lead a more fulfilling life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aSciencexPhilosophy. 7aSCIENCE / Philosophy & Social Aspects.2bisacsh  aAccuracy and precision.  aAnecdotal evidence.  aAppeal to emotion.  aAvailability.  aBehavioural sciences.  aBillionaire.  aBody of knowledge.  aCertainty.  aChemist.  aCognitive dissonance.  aConfirmation bias.  aConspiracy theory.  aConvenience.  aCosmological constant.  aCultural relativism.  aDiscovery (observation).  aEchinus esculentus.  aEducation.  aEfficacy.  aEmpathy.  aEmpirical evidence.  aEveryday life.  aExplanation.  aFact.  aFixation (histology).  aHumility.  aHypothesis.  aIT Works.  aIdeology.  aIllusory superiority.  aInvention.  aKnow thyself.  aLogical reasoning.  aMoral relativism.  aNatural science.  aNature of Science.  aObjectivity (philosophy).  aObjectivity (science).  aObservation.  aPhenomenon.  aPhilosophy of science.  aPhysicist.  aPrediction.  aPrince Charming.  aQuantum mechanics.  aRationality.  aReal image.  aReality.  aReason.  aReproducibility.  aResult.  aScience.  aScientific enterprise.  aScientific evidence.  aScientific literacy.  aScientific method.  aScientific realism.  aScientific theory.  aScientist.  aSense of wonder.  aSpecial relativity.  aSustainable living.  aTechnology.  aThe Better Angels of Our Nature.  aThe Nature of Truth.  aTheoretical physics.  aTheory.  aUncertainty.  aUnderstanding.  aWishful thinking.  aWorld view.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe 